################################################################################
# MVP 7 — TESTING, DOCUMENTATION & DEPLOYMENT
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Goal: Finalize the platform — test everything, document it, and deploy to prod
# Reference: Documentation costs — API integration guide, project book, PPT
################################################################################

## PHASE 1: Backend Testing (Node.js)
[ ] Set up testing framework:
    [ ] Jest + Supertest (HTTP integration tests)
    [ ] Create /tests folder with /unit and /integration subfolders
[ ] Write unit tests:
    [ ] Auth service: signup, login, JWT token generation, bcrypt hashing
    [ ] Resume parser: PDF/DOCX text extraction, AI parse response validation
    [ ] Match score engine: scoring weights, edge cases (no skills, 100% match)
    [ ] Job service: create, update, fetch jobs from MongoDB
[ ] Write integration tests (API route tests):
    [ ] POST /api/auth/signup → 201, 409 (duplicate email), 400 (validation fail)
    [ ] POST /api/auth/login → 200, 401 (wrong password), 404 (user not found)
    [ ] POST /api/user/resumes → 201 (uploaded), 400 (invalid type), 413 (too large)
    [ ] POST /api/jobs/:id/apply → 201, 403 (unauthenticated), 409 (already applied)
    [ ] GET /api/recruiter/jobs/:id/applicants → 200 with sorted list by match score
[ ] Achieve minimum 70% code coverage on core business logic
[ ] Set up test MongoDB database:
    [ ] Use mongodb-memory-server for in-memory MongoDB in unit tests
    [ ] Use separate MongoDB Atlas test cluster for integration tests

## PHASE 2: Frontend Testing
[ ] Set up Vitest + React Testing Library
[ ] Write component tests:
    [ ] SignupPage: renders form, validates inputs, submits correctly
    [ ] LoginPage: renders form, displays error on invalid credentials
    [ ] JobCard: renders job data, shows correct match score badge
    [ ] ResumeUpload: drag-and-drop works, shows progress, handles errors
    [ ] ProtectedRoute: redirects unauthenticated users to /login
[ ] Write end-to-end (E2E) tests with Playwright:
    [ ] Signup as Job Seeker flow (form → submit → dashboard redirect)
    [ ] Upload resume and view AI analysis results
    [ ] Apply to a job and see it in "Applied" section
    [ ] Recruiter: create a job post and view applicants
    [ ] Recruiter: shortlist a candidate
[ ] Set up E2E tests to run against staging environment

## PHASE 3: Performance & Security Audit
[ ] Run Lighthouse audit on landing page:
    [ ] Target: Performance ≥ 90, Accessibility ≥ 90, SEO ≥ 90
    [ ] Fix any failing audits
[ ] Optimize frontend bundle:
    [ ] Code splitting (lazy load dashboard routes)
    [ ] Image optimization (WebP format, lazy loading)
    [ ] Gzip/Brotli compression (via CDN)
[ ] Backend security checklist:
    [ ] All inputs validated and sanitized (prevent SQL injection, XSS)
    [ ] Passwords hashed with bcrypt (never stored plain text)
    [ ] Rate limiting on auth, upload, and AI endpoints
    [ ] CORS whitelist: only production domain allowed
    [ ] Secrets never hardcoded (all in .env)
    [ ] HTTPS enforced (no HTTP in production)
    [ ] File upload: validate MIME type (not just extension), scan for malware if needed
    [ ] JWT tokens expire appropriately
[ ] Load testing with k6 or Artillery:
    [ ] Simulate 100 concurrent users
    [ ] Verify API response < 500ms under load

## PHASE 4: API Documentation
[ ] Set up Swagger/OpenAPI docs (swagger-jsdoc + swagger-ui-express):
    [ ] Auto-generate from JSDoc/docstring annotations
    [ ] Available at: /api/docs (development only)
[ ] Document all API endpoints:
    [ ] Auth APIs (signup, login, logout, refresh, /me)
    [ ] User APIs (profile, resume, applications)
    [ ] Recruiter APIs (jobs, applicants, shortlist)
    [ ] AI APIs (parse resume, match score)
    [ ] Public APIs (job listings, skills autocomplete)
[ ] Include in each endpoint doc:
    [ ] Method + path
    [ ] Auth required? (Bearer token role)
    [ ] Request body schema (JSON example)
    [ ] Response schema (JSON example)
    [ ] Error responses (400, 401, 403, 404, 409, 500)
[ ] Export Postman collection:
    [ ] Create Postman workspace with environment variables
    [ ] Add all API requests with example request/response bodies
    [ ] Export as `API-Collection.json` and commit to repo
[ ] Create API Integration Guide document (`docs/API-Integration-Guide.md`):
    [ ] Authentication flow (how to get + use JWT tokens)
    [ ] File upload instructions (multipart form-data)
    [ ] AI API usage and limits
    [ ] Error handling reference table
    [ ] Rate limiting headers explanation
    [ ] Code examples (JavaScript fetch, Python requests)

