## PHASE 7: Production Deployment
[ ] Set up staging environment (mirror of production):
    [ ] Same hosting, separate DB, .env.staging
[ ] Deploy backend — Render.com:
    [ ] Create "Web Service" on Render (render.com)
    [ ] Connect GitHub repo → select backend/ folder
    [ ] Environment: Node
    [ ] Build command: `npm install`
    [ ] Start command: `node server.js`
    [ ] Add all environment variables in Render dashboard:
        [ ] MONGODB_URI (MongoDB Atlas connection string)
        [ ] JWT_SECRET, REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET
        [ ] OPENAI_API_KEY
        [ ] AWS / Cloudinary storage credentials
        [ ] RESEND_API_KEY, EMAIL_FROM
        [ ] REDIS_URL (Upstash Redis)
        [ ] FRONTEND_URL (Vercel URL for CORS)
    [ ] Enable auto-deploy on push to main
    [ ] Verify health check: GET /api/health → 200 OK
[ ] Deploy frontend — Vercel:
    [ ] Connect GitHub repo to Vercel (vercel.com)
    [ ] Set root directory to frontend/ in project settings
    [ ] Add env var: VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com
    [ ] Add custom domain (yourdomain.com) in Vercel
    [ ] Enable auto-deploy on push to main (via Vercel GitHub integration)
[ ] Deploy Bull workers (Redis job queue):
    [ ] Bull workers run as part of the Node.js backend process on Render
    [ ] Ensure REDIS_URL (Upstash) is set in Render env vars
    [ ] Verify resume parsing queue processes jobs after upload
[ ] Configure DNS:
    [ ] yourdomain.com → Vercel frontend
    [ ] api.yourdomain.com → backend (CNAME or A record)
[ ] Enable HTTPS (auto via Vercel + Render Let's Encrypt)
[ ] Run full smoke test on production:
    [ ] Sign up as user → upload resume → apply to job → see match score ✓
    [ ] Sign up as recruiter → post job → view applicants → shortlist ✓
    [ ] Landing page loads < 3 seconds ✓
    [ ] AI analysis completes within 60 seconds ✓
[ ] Set up uptime monitoring (UptimeRobot free tier):
    [ ] Monitor /api/health every 5 minutes
    [ ] Email alert on downtime

## PHASE 8: CI/CD Pipeline Setup
[ ] Create `.github/workflows/ci.yml`:
    [ ] Trigger on PR to main branch
    [ ] Steps: checkout, install deps, run lint, run unit tests
    [ ] Block merge if any step fails
[ ] Create `.github/workflows/deploy-backend.yml`:
    [ ] Trigger on push to main
    [ ] Render auto-deploys via GitHub integration (no manual Docker push needed)
[ ] Create `.github/workflows/deploy-frontend.yml`:
    [ ] Trigger on push to main
    [ ] Vercel auto-deploy handles this (GitHub integration)

## PHASE 9: Post-Launch Checklist
[ ] Monitor error logs for first 48 hours (Sentry / Render logs dashboard)
[ ] Check email delivery success rate
[ ] Verify AI resume parsing working correctly on 5 real test resumes
[ ] Monitor API response times (target: < 500ms for 95th percentile)
[ ] Gather feedback from 2 test recruiters + 3 test job seekers
[ ] Create GitHub Issues for any bugs found

## DELIVERABLES / ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
[ ] All unit tests pass (> 70% coverage)
[ ] All E2E test scenarios pass on staging
[ ] Swagger API docs accessible at /api/docs
[ ] Postman collection exported and committed
[ ] API Integration Guide document complete
[ ] Project book written (all chapters)
[ ] PPT presentation complete (15-20 slides)
[ ] Production deployment live and accessible via custom domain
[ ] HTTPS enforced on all endpoints
[ ] Uptime monitoring configured
[ ] CI/CD pipeline running on GitHub
[ ] All environment variables set in production (no secrets in code)
